2 HOUSE BILL 1334
1 (2) The advertisement for bids shall appear at least a week prior to the date
2 on which bids are to be filed.
3 (3) Any contract of sale shall be awarded to the highest responsible bidder,
4 and any contract of purchase shall be awarded to the lowest responsible bidder, but the
5 County Commissioners shall have the right to reject any and all bids.
6 (4) Any contract entered into in violation of the provisions of this section
7 shall be null and void. The provisions of this section shall not apply to necessary repairs
8 made in case of emergency.
9 (5) THE COUNTY COMMISSIONERS, OR ANY EMPLOYEE OF GARRETT
10 COUNTY, MAY ENTER INTO A PURCHASE OR WORK PROJECT CONTRACT FOR AN
11 INDETERMINATE AMOUNT OF GOODS OR SERVICES PROCURED ON AN AS–NEEDED
12 BASIS OVER A PERIOD OF TIME WITHOUT ADVERTISING FOR BIDS UNDER
13 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS DIVISION. THIS PARAGRAPH APPLIES REGARDLESS OF
14 WHETHER THE CUMULATIVE TOTAL EXCEEDS $50,000.
15 (6) THE COUNTY COMMISSIONERS, OR ANY EMPLOYEE OF GARRETT
16 COUNTY, MAY ENTER INTO A CONTRACT FOR THE PURCHASE OF ONE OR MORE
17 VEHICLES FOR AN AMOUNT UP TO $100,000 WITHOUT ADVERTISING FOR BIDS
18 UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS DIVISION.
19 [(5)] (7) If any County Commissioner shall violate any provisions of this
20 division, the Commissioner shall be liable to indictment, and, upon conviction, shall forfeit
21 the office.
22 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
23 October 1, 2025.

